Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a novel text-based visual SLAM method that integrates text objects into the visual SLAM pipeline. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The accurate 3D text maps produced by the proposed method could be useful for navigation and scene understanding in robotic applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper describes the use of semantic meanings of text features in the proposed method, which could be considered as an AI-related aspect. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions the use of illumination-invariant photometric error to integrate text features into visual SLAM, which could involve machine learning techniques. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with text objects and their semantic meanings, which could be related to natural language processing and computational linguistics.
